class KadasAnnotationStyleEditor : QWidget
{
%Docstring(signature="appended")
Per-type style editor widget for a stock :py:class:`QgsAnnotationItem`.

Concrete subclasses build the type-specific styling row (e.g. shape size
/ fill / stroke for markers, font / size / color / buffer for point
text) and translate between item state and widget state. The map tool
that hosts the bottom bar simply asks the controller for an editor and
connects to its two signals.

Two signals separate live preview from committed edits: - \c
:py:func:`~previewChanged` fires for every interim change (e.g. a
keystroke in the text field). The host should re-apply state to the item
and refresh the layer, but should not push a new history entry. - \c
:py:func:`~committed` fires when a discrete edit is finalized. The host
should apply, refresh, push history, and persist the style.
%End

%TypeHeaderCode
#include "kadas/gui/annotationitems/kadasannotationstyleeditor.h"
%End
  public:

    virtual void loadFromItem( const QgsAnnotationItem *item ) = 0;
%Docstring
Populates the widgets from ``item``'s current state.
%End

    virtual void applyToItem( QgsAnnotationItem *item ) const = 0;
%Docstring
Writes the widgets' state back into ``item``.
%End

  signals:
    void previewChanged();
%Docstring
Emitted continuously while the user is interacting (live preview).
%End
    void committed();
%Docstring
Emitted when a discrete edit is finalized (push history + persist).
%End
};



